snippet: The six-time Olympic gold medalist Amy Van Dyken-Rouen left the hospital in Englewood, Colo., and said she was feeling “1,000 times better” after two months of rehabilitation.
abstract: Olympic swimmer Amy Van Dyken-Rouen leaves hospital in Englewood, Colo, after two months of rehabilitation; was paralyzed just below the waist in all-terrain vehicle crash on June 6 in Arizona.
lead_paragraph: The six-time Olympic gold medalist Amy Van Dyken-Rouen left the hospital in Englewood, Colo., and said she was feeling “1,000 times better” after two months of rehabilitation.
